<%
def url(page, params = nil)
  @base_url + "?page=" + page + (params ? "&#{params}" : "")
end

def time(t)
  return '---' unless t

  t.localtime.strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S')
end

def value(v)
  v.nil? || v.to_s.empty? ? '---' : v
end

zone = @object.dns_zone
server = @object.dns_server
-%>
Hi <%= @user.login %>,

secondary DNS server <%= server.name %> cannot transfer zone <%= zone.name %>
from your primary DNS server.

Primary server: <%= value(@object.last_transfer_primary_addr) %>
Last attempt: <%= time(@object.last_transfer_at) %>
Error code: <%= value(@object.last_transfer_reason_code) %>
Reason: <%= value(@object.last_transfer_reason) %>

Until the transfer succeeds, our DNS servers will keep serving the last
successfully loaded version of the zone. Please fix the zone contents or allow
AXFR from the primary server to our secondary server.

You can view zone transfer logs in vpsAdmin:

  <%= url('dns', "action=transfer_log&dns_server_zone=#{@object.id}") %>

If you acknowledge this issue, you will not receive more alerts until it is
detected again after being resolved:

  <%= url('monitoring', "action=ack&id=#{@event.id}") %>

Best regards,

vpsFree.cz team

(This is an automated mail from vpsAdmin, your reply will be sent to our support)
